07/09/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- NATO Secretary General Lord George Robertson told participants at a security conference in Sofia on Friday (5 September) that the Balkans should crack down on organised crime and corruption. He acknowledged that "the countries of Southeast Europe have made considerable progress these last few years in getting their houses in order, implementing difficult but necessary reforms and moving closer to Euro-Atlantic structures." He also called on the international community to reaffirm its commitment to the development of the Balkans. Robertson, who is stepping down from NATO's top post in December, is currently on a farewell tour of Southeast Europe.The conference in Sofia was attended by the defence ministers of Albania, Croatia, Macedonia, Romania, Serbia-Montenegro, and Turkey. (AFP, BTA, Mediapool, news.bg, MIA - 05/09/03)
